<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id4d66b060-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d" identifier="/us/usc/t34/s60906"><num value="60906">§ 60906.</num><heading> Data collection</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id4d66b061-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d" identifier="/us/usc/t34/s60906/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> In general</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Beginning on the date that is three years after <date date="2022-08-03">August 3, 2022</date>, and annually thereafter, the Director of the National Institute of Justice shall publish statistics on the number of cold case murders.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id4d66b062-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d" identifier="/us/usc/t34/s60906/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Manner of publication</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The statistics published pursuant to subsection (a) shall, at a minimum, be disaggregated by the circumstances of the cold case murder, including the classification of the offense, and by agency.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id4d66b063-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d">(<ref href="/us/pl/117/164/s7">Pub. L. 117–164, § 7</ref>, <date date="2022-08-03">Aug. 3, 2022</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/136/1360">136 Stat. 1360</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
